4. Containerization with Docker
Create a Dockerfile to containerize the Flask API and the ML model:

# Dockerfile
FROM python:3.9-slim

# Set the working directory
WORKDIR /app

# Copy the Flask app and ML model
COPY app.py /app/
COPY model /app/model/

# Install required packages
RUN pip install --no-cache-dir flask mlflow scikit-learn numpy

# Expose the API port
EXPOSE 5000

# Run the Flask app
CMD ["python", "app.py"]
To build the Docker image and run the container:

docker build -t iris_model_api .
docker run -p 5000:5000 iris_model_api